{{Infobox writer <!--For more information, see [[:Template:Infobox Writer/doc]].--> | name = Ashlee Vance | image = Ashlee Vance.gk.jpg | caption = Ashlee Vance, at a signing for ''Elon Musk''. | birth_date = {{birth year and age|1977}} | birth_place = [[South Africa]] | education = [[Pomona College]] | website = [http://www.theduckrabbit.com The Duckrabbit] | subjects = Technology, business | notablework = ''Elon Musk: Tesla, SpaceX, and the Quest for a Fantastic Future'' (2015) }}
'''Ashlee Vance''' (born 1977) is an American business columnist and author.
He is well known for his biography about [[Elon Musk]] entitled ''[[Elon Musk: Tesla, SpaceX, and the Quest for a Fantastic Future]].''<ref>{{Triangulation|203|Ashlee Vance}}</ref> The book was released on May 19, 2015.
==Work== Vance was primarily known for writing for ''[[The Register]]'' from March 2003<ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.theregister.co.uk/2003/03/24/sun_adopts_write_once_revise/ | date = 2003-03-24 | title = Sun adopts Write Once, Revise Anywhere license | first = Ashlee | last = Vance | work = The Register }}</ref> to August 2008,<ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.theregister.co.uk/2008/08/21/av_off/ | date = 2008-08-21 | title = ''Reg'' server and chip hack molested by Gray Lady | first = Ashlee | last = Vance | work = The Register }}</ref> but moved to ''[[The New York Times]]'' in September 2008<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/author/ashlee-vance/|title=Ashlee Vance - Bits - The New York Times|website=bits.blogs.nytimes.com|access-date=2016-04-10}}</ref> and then to [[Bloomberg Businessweek]] in January 2011.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ashlee Vance and Brendan Greeley Join Bloomberg Businessweek|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-01-05/ashlee-vance-and-brendan-greeley-join-bloomberg-businessweek.html|work=Press Release|publisher=Bloomberg|accessdate=8 April 2011|date=2011-01-05}}</ref> Vance covered companies such as [[IBM]], [[Hewlett-Packard|HP]], [[Intel]], and [[Dell]], and also writes about a wide range of technology topics, including robots, [[Segway PT|Segway]] scooters, and the [[R (programming language)|R programming language]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Data Analysts Captivated by R’s Power|url=http://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2009/01/08/r-you-ready-for-r|publisher=The New York Times|accessdate=2013-09-13|date=2009-01-08}}</ref>
In 2007 Vance wrote a book, called ''Geek Silicon Valley'', on the history of the [[Silicon Valley]].<ref>{{cite book | title = Geek Silicon Valley | publisher = Globe Pequot Press | first = Ashlee | last = Vance | isbn = 978-0-7627-4239-4 | date = 2007-11-01 }}</ref> In 2015 he published a biography of [[Elon Musk]] <ref>http://time.com/money/3860353/elon-musk-biography/</ref> His writing often also appears in such publications as ''[[The Economist]]'', ''[[Chicago Tribune]]'', [[CNN.com]], ''[[The Globe and Mail]]'', the ''[[International Herald Tribune]]'', and [[CNET]].
Vance hosted an audio [[podcast]] called ''Semi-Coherent Computing'' from 2007–2008,<ref>[https://www.theregister.co.uk/hardware/semi_coherent/ Semi-Coherent Computing]</ref> in which he discussed enterprise computing topics such as [[Datacenter]] cooling and [[blade server]]s, and interviewed guests including chip pioneer David Ditzel of [[Transmeta]], [[Sun Microsystems]], and [[Bell Labs]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.edge.org/3rd_culture/bios/ditzel.html | work = The Third Culture | publisher = Edge Foundation, Inc | title = David R. Ditzel }}</ref>
In 2015, Vance started writing and hosting the "Hello World" video series for Bloomberg, focusing on the tech scene in various countries.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/features/2016-hello-world/|title=Goodbye, Silicon Valley. Hello World|website=Bloomberg.com|access-date=2016-04-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.reddit.com/r/technology/comments/4bn3mz/hi_im_ashlee_vance_host_of_a_show_called_hello/|title=Ashlee Vance AMA on reddit|website=reddit|access-date=2016-04-10}}</ref> In the same year, he published his biography about [[Elon Musk]], the founder of [[Tesla, Inc.|Tesla]], [[SpaceX]], [[PayPal]] and other tech companies.
