{{expand language|topic=|langcode=de|otherarticle=Wolfgang Dürheimer|date=September 2017}} {{more citations needed|date=September 2017}} {{Infobox person | birth_date = {{birth year and age|1958}} | nationality = Germany | spouse = |image=Wolfgang Durheimer, IAA 2017, Frankfurt (1Y7A2150).jpg |caption= Dürrheimer at IAA 2017 | birth_place = [[Martinszell im Allgäu]] | death_place = | other_names = | occupation = | alma_mater= University of Applied Sciences, Munich | years_active = | known_for = | notable_works =
}} '''Wolfgang Dürheimer''' (born 20 June 1958) is a German automotive business executive who, until January 2018, was the President of Bugatti Automobiles S.A.S. He was the former Executive Vice President of Research and Development at Porsche AG.
== Life ==
He was born in [[:de:Martinszell im Allgäu|Upper Bavaria]] on 20 June 1958.
He has a degree in Automotive Engineering and a Post Graduate degree in Engineering Business Management from the University of Applied Sciences, Munich.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bentleymedia.com/en/Company/Executive%20Team/wolfgang%20durheimer|title=BENTLEY NEWSROOM : wolfgang durheimer|work=bentleymedia.com|accessdate=11 March 2017}}</ref>
== Career ==
He also has been the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer at Bentley Motors Limited and President of Bugatti Automobiles S.A.S. since June 1, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/private/person.asp?personId=8339715&privcapId=377732|title=Wolfgang Dürheimer: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg|work=bloomberg.com|accessdate=11 March 2017}}</ref>
He has received a [[Fulbright Program|Fulbright scholarship]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://press.porsche.com/archive/executives/de/durheimer/|title=Wolfgang Dürheimer|work=porsche.com|accessdate=11 March 2017}}</ref>
